-- Japanese Bought Net 353.1 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   M i n h   B u i
-- 2012-07-11T23:51:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-11/japanese-bought-net-353-1-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended July 6 according
to figures based on reports from designated major investors
released by the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 353.1 billion yen ($4.4 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, bought 10.3 billion yen in overseas stocks
and bought 31.2 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 394.6 billion yen.  Foreign investors sold 20.7 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
sold 3.6 billion yen in stocks, and bought 1536.5 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 1512.2
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
